   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   SALTER-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ In June of 1975, when I took a
job as a sports writer at the San Francisco Examiner, I would have
been amazed (and appalled) had anyone told me I'd still be here
when the 24th anniversary of my hire date rolled around. By
STEPHANIE SALTER.
</P>
<P>
   PERSONAL-WEATHER-PERSON (San Ramon, Calif.) _ Any bozo with a
thermometer and a pointer can lick his finger, stick it in the wind
and predict the weather, but I need more: a meteorologist I can
bond with. I need a middle-aged, European/South American,
curly-haired, pre-menopausal weather analyst who understands the
chafing of heat rash, the sorrow of sweat stains and the anguish of
the frizzy blues. By EILEEN MITCHELL.
</P>
<P>
   INDONESIA (Jakarta, Indonesia) _ What fascinates me about
Indonesia are glaring contradictions, either apparent or real, of
the Indonesian psyche (or at least the people on the island of
Java, which has 60 percent of the population and most of the
powerful politicians). By AL HIRSHEN.
</P>
