but mamma.com prides itself on accuracy. While that in itself is
probably not enough to earn a link, we can't help falling in love
with the site's mascot, a animated, matronly gray haired woman who
reminds us of Aunt Bea and the farmer's wife from the film,
``Babe.'' We love mamma.com, but more to the point, we love Mamma.
</P>
<P>
   ianrwww.unl.edu/ianr/pat/ephome.htm _ Pesticides have been in
the news lately, and this site, the University of Nebraska's
Pesticide Education Resources, has information on safety,
regulations, laws, agriculture and environmental protection.
</P>
