 &HT;    Invent ways to cool down
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ The Department of Energy and the Owens Corning company
are asking rising fourth-, fifth- and sixth-graders to draw an
original energy-saving device and describe how it works in 100
words or less. Four winners will be chosen to go to the EnergySmart
Schools Inventor Summit in December. They'll also win a $250
savings bond and a trip to an Energy Department lab to build their
inventions.
</P>
<P>
   See www.eren.doe.gov/energysmartschools for details.
