<HEADER>
A8334 &Cx1f; ttj-z
r t BC-HILL-COUNTRY-INFO-HNS     06-19 0630
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HILL-COUNTRY-INFO-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;     WHERE TO STAY IN THE TEXAS HILL COUNTRY 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     By HARRY SHATTUCK  
 &HT;     c.2000 Houston Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Texas Hill Country has resorts that will satisfy a wide
variety of vacation objectives.
</P>
<P>
   Among them:
</P>
<P>
   Just outside Bandera, the 543-acre Flying L Guest Ranch
emphasizes a cowboy motif _ yes, horseback riding is a favorite
activity _ but also features an 18-hole championship golf course, a
pro shop, lighted tennis and basketball courts, a swimming pool and
fine dining.
</P>
<P>
   Summer programs for ages 3-12 range from goat roping and calf
scrambles to rock painting and pony rides.
</P>
<P>
   The ranch's 41 suites and free-standing villas include bedroom
and sitting room, refrigerator, microwave and other amenities.
</P>
<P>
   It's located 1 1/2 miles south of Bandera on Texas 173. Call
800-292-5134 or access www.flyingl.com.
</P>
<P>
   Lake Austin Spa Resort is rated a top 10 destination spa by the
Zagat Survey of U.S. Hotels, Resorts and Spas.
</P>
<P>
   The resort offers a wide range of programs dedicated to a
healthy lifestyle. Its fourth annual series on healthy cooking,
presented during several weeks through August, features popular
chef Terry Conlan (author of Lean Star Cuisine) and guest chefs.
</P>
<P>
   Guest rooms are scattered about the property, and many afford
views of the lake. Overnight packages can include lodging, three
meals daily, spa services, fitness classes and life-enhancement
programs.
</P>
<P>
   The resort's tranquil lakeside setting is off RR 620 northwest
of Austin. Call 800-847-5637 or access www.lakeaustin.com.
</P>
<P>
   Canyon of the Eagles Lodge and Nature Park, billed as Texas'
first large eco-resort, occupies 940 acres on the north shore of
Lake Buchanan, northwest of Austin.
</P>
<P>
   Amid this preserve with abundant wildlife is a 64-room lodge _
actually an 18-building compound _ where guests unwind in rocking
chairs on porches and watch as birds feed and deer pass nearby.
Naturalists conduct frequent programs, and an observatory
encourages stargazing.
</P>
<P>
   This is also the new home of the Vanishing Texas River Cruise.
Camping and RV facilities are available, as are canoe and kayak
rentals. The lodge offers full-service dining.
</P>
<P>
   Canyon of the Eagles Lodge is located at the end of RR 2341,
about 18 miles northwest of Burnet. Call 800-977-0081 or access
www.canyonoftheeagles.com.
</P>
<P>
   With the recent completion of the Ridge Course, Tapatio Springs
Golf Resort and Conference Center near Boerne touts 27 holes of
championship play. Its original course is one of Texas' 10 best,
according to several surveys.
</P>
<P>
   The resort has 148 rooms and suites, all renovated last year.
Other features include a fine-dining restaurant, a pool, a fitness
center, tennis courts and nearby fishing lakes.
</P>
<P>
   Tapatio Springs is on Deep Hollow Road just off FM 46, about
four miles west of Boerne. Call 800-999-3299 or access
www.tapatio.com on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   About eight miles northwest of Boerne, the 377-acre Guadalupe
River Ranch offers hiking, horseback riding, tubing, golf
privileges at several area courses, and one of the Hill Country's
most popular full-service spas.
</P>
<P>
   The ranch has 48 guest rooms, and packages include three meals
daily in a restaurant that attracts many area residents.
</P>
<P>
   This one-time home of actress Olivia de Havilland is located on
FM 474.
</P>
<P>
   Call 830-537-4837 or access www.guadaluperiverranch.com.
</P>
<P>
   The Hill Country region is home to hundreds of
bed-and-breakfasts, guest houses and other intimate lodgings.
Chambers of commerce and visitors bureaus are good sources of
information. Also contact Historic and Hospitality Accommodations
of Texas, whose members must adhere to high standards. Call
800-428-0368 or access www.hat.org.
</P>
</TEXT>
