<HEADLINE>
&HT;     HILL COUNTRY RESORT SPECIALIZES IN FAMILY FUN 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (EDs: With HILL-COUNTRY-INFO)  
 &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     By HARRY SHATTUCK  
 &HT;     c.2000 Houston Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN ANTONIO _ Looking for an antidote to the early summer heat?
</P>
<P>
   Sink into an antique rocking chair on Aunt Mary's Porch. Float
along the 950-foot Ramblin' River. Saunter down a
three-quarter-mile nature trail, spying for native plants beneath
stately live oak trees.
</P>
<P>
   It's all part of the family fun at the Hyatt Regency Hill
Country Resort, a favorite San Antonio retreat since its debut
seven years ago and now fresh from a $3.5 million enhancement.
</P>
<P>
   More is on the way: A 15,000-square-foot spa, planned for
completion late this year, will include up to 20 private treatment
rooms; lounges with steam, sauna and whirlpool; a lap pool; and a
beauty salon.
</P>
<P>
   The 200-acre resort, amid wildflower meadows and
limestone-banked creeks 16 miles northwest of downtown San Antonio,
just a short distance from Sea World, has received AAA's
four-diamond rating and Mobil Travel Guide's four-star designation
each year since 1995.
</P>
<P>
   Recreational facilities include a challenging 18-hole golf
course designed by Arthur Hills, three tennis courts, volleyball
courts, bicycles available for rent, paths for bikers and joggers,
a health club, Camp Hyatt for ages 3-12, and four acres reserved
for water enthusiasts.
</P>
<P>
   Kids and parents alike enjoy tubing on the Ramblin' River, a
mini-version of experiences on the Guadalupe and other Hill Country
rivers. Two swimming pools are separated by a waterfall. An open
deck is designed for sunbathing.
</P>
<P>
   The resort's 500 guest rooms and suites _ each with new bedding,
carpet, drapes and wall coverings _ are in nine wings that form
scenic courtyards. All rooms have refrigerators, irons and ironing
boards, and coffee makers. Twenty-six rooms are designed for guests
with disabilities.
</P>
<P>
   Billed as ``the finest little ranch house in Texas,'' the main
lobby has comfortable seating beside two fireplaces and opens onto
Aunt Mary's Porch, where many guests relax with or without a glass
of Luckenbach Lemonade (gin, peach schnapps, cranberry juice, and
sweet and sour) or ``Texas tea'' (sweetened with an elixir more
potent than sugar).
</P>
<P>
   Fine dining is available Tuesday through Sunday evenings in
Antler's Lodge. Innovative starters during a recent visit included
a barbecued duck and mango quesadilla ($7.75), rattlesnake fritters
($7.50) and a ravioli of pheasant and foie gras ($8.50). Among
intriguing entrees: a trio of grilled beef medallion,
pumpkin-seed-crusted lamb chop and Texas venison ($28.50).
</P>
<P>
   On the second Friday of each month except December, Antler's
private dining room is the setting for a Winemaker's Dinner. Wine
tastings featuring different regions begin at 7 p.m.; then chefs
offer course-by-course food presentations paired with fine wines.
(Cost is $70, plus gratuity; call 210-520-4037 for reservations.)
The Springhouse Cafe is a winner, too, for breakfast, lunch, dinner
and weekend buffets. Light fare and beverages are served during the
day at Big Ed's Pool House. The General Store stocks deli
sandwiches and cookies.
</P>
<P>
   Lodging rates vary depending on season and availability but
generally range from $195 to $365 for deluxe rooms, with suites
starting at $315.
</P>
<P>
   A private wing houses Hyatt's Regency Club services. Golf
packages are available; rates start at $152.50 for one golfer and
$182 for two (each based on double occupancy) and include 18 holes,
cart and daily breakfast.
</P>
<P>
   As at most other resorts, convention business can be brisk; the
resort has more than 27,000 square feet of meeting space.
</P>
<P>
   The Hyatt Regency Hill Country Resort is located at 9800 Hyatt
Resort Drive, just off the Westside Expressway and a short distance
from Loop 1604. Call the resort directly at 210-647-1234; call
Hyatt Hotels and Resorts at 800-223-1234; or access
www.sanantonio.hyatt.com on the Internet for a useful site with
sample menus, photos and other information.
</P>
</TEXT>
