   FLA-SKULVOUCHERS _ PENSACOLA, Fla. _ There's optimism in
Pensacola. For now, the city has the only two schools in the state
rated low enough to make students eligilble for tax-supported
school vouchers. Results from standardized state tests are due back
Monday (6/19) and Spencer Bibbs and Dixon elementary schools may
come off the list_or be joined by hundreds of schools across
Florida. Groups on both sides of the issue will be watching for the
results. Months ago, a state court judge ruled the voucher program
violated the state constititution. The issue has been appealed to
