probable-cause hearing begins June 20, and the man considered most
responsible for bringing first-degree murder charges against the
Kennedy cousin is Mark Fuhrman. By Brian MacQuarrie. 1850 words.
</P>
<P>
   VICTIM-ADVOCATES (Undated) _ Recent violence has spurred new
calls for the death penalty. But victim advocate groups say
vengeance isn't the answer. By Francie Latour. 1390 words.
</P>
<P>
   RADCLIFFE-FAUST (Cambridge, Mass.) _ Drew Gilpin Faust, incoming
dean of the Radcliffe Institute For Advanced Study, is in the
vanguard of a small band of women who are Civil War scholars of
standing. By Sam Allis. 1670 words. PHOTO
</P>
