form of payment accepted.
</P>
<P>
   The Grove (2250), a popular locals hangout, is a friendly place
to stop for morning coffee or breakfast _ and it will keep you out
of a cookie-cutter Starbucks down the street. The Grove offers six
different gourmet coffee drinks daily. Be advised that the
breakfast menu leans heavily toward vegetarian items.
</P>
<P>
   For heartier fare at breakfast or lunch, it's hard to beat
Judy's Cafe (2268). The portions are substantial and diverse,
including a breakfast scramble featuring smoked salmon, Bermuda
onions and cream cheese. Andale Taqueria (2150) can also attack a
robust appetite with its mesquite-grill Mexican items.
</P>
<P>
   If you're looking for sandwiches for a picnic on the grounds of
the Presidio, the best option is probably Lucca Delicatessen
(2120), an Old World deli that is worth a stop just for the rich
smells within. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
