<P>
   WEBMD_ Healtheon announced it has ponied up more money for its
merger and agreed to surrender more control: Under the revised
merger agreements, Healtheon/WebMD will issue 2.5 shares of
Healtheon/WebMD common stock for each share of Medical Manager. The
exchange ratio for CareInsite remains at the originally announced
1.3 shares of Healtheon/WebMD common stock for each share of
CareInsite not owned by Medical Manager. (Kanell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   RADIO-TOPMARKET _ ATLANTA _ Traffic jams, a shortage of radio
stations, and advertisers with fat wallets have something in
common. They are making Atlanta's fragmented radio market
especially attractive to broadcasters trying to control more of the
dial. ``Atlanta is the radio beachfront property. It's not unusual
to pay a premium for it,'' says John Hogan, an Atlanta-based senior
vice president for Clear Channel Communications. One of his
competitors -- Cox Radio, which already operates five of Atlanta's
15 top stations -- recently signed a deal to acquire fourth-ranked
Kiss 104.7. The station's $280 million price tag apparently is the
highest ever paid in Atlanta, competing broadcasters say. (Kempner,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30.
</P>
