<HEADLINE>
WORLD MUSIC HIGHLIGHTS
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Eds: For use with Hollywood Bowl world music package) 
By REED JOHNSON 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Classical and pops music fans take heed. This summer you'll be
able to get your usual fix of Rachmaninoff and Rosemary Clooney.
But your friends and neighbors may be moving to the beat of
Romanian flute music or blissing out to (ital) qawwali (ital) in a
downtown amphitheatre. Here's a few upcoming world music
highlights, listed by venue:
</P>
<P>
   ``World Festival 2000,'' Hollywood Bowl, (323) 850-2000.
</P>
<P>
   June 25 _ ``Fiery Flamenco,'' Noche Flamenca, Thierry
Robin-Gitans, Del Monte Flamenco/Anjani's Kathak.
</P>
<P>
   July 16 _ ``Global Divas,'' Miriam Makeba and Albita.
</P>
<P>
   July 30 _ ``Celtic Journeys,'' Natalie MacMaster, Altan,
Kennelly Irish Dancers.
</P>
<P>
   July 23 _ ``World Blues Party,'' Koko Taylor and Her Blues
Machine, Ali Farka Toure, hosted by Bonnie Raitt.
</P>
<P>
   Aug. 6 _ ``African Funk Sensations,'' Maceo Parker, Femi
Anikulapo Kuti &AMP; The Positive Force.
</P>
<P>
   Sept. 10 _ ``Celebrate Brazil,'' Jorge Ben Jor, Daniela Mercury.
</P>
<P>
   Summer Nights Season 2000, John Anson Ford Amphitheatre,
Hollywood, (323) 461-3673.
</P>
<P>
   July 9 _ The Klezmatics
</P>
<P>
   Aug. 20 _ African Village Music Festival
</P>
<P>
   Sept. 16, 17 _ Elba Ramalho &AMP; Geraldo Azevedo
</P>
<P>
   Grand Performances at the California Plaza Watercourt, (213)
587-2159.
</P>
<P>
   June 29 _ Hugh Masekela
</P>
<P>
   July 14 _ La Bottine Souriante
</P>
<P>
   July 15 _ Joaquin Diaz
</P>
<P>
   July 22 T.V. Ramprasad and Lakshmi Shankar
</P>
<P>
   Aug. 3 _ Rizwan-Muazzam Party
</P>
<P>
   Aug. 18 _ Johnny Polanco y Conjunto Amistad
</P>
<P>
   Sept. 1 _ Fantcha
</P>
<P>
   Oct. 25 _ Ballet Folclorico do Brasil
</P>
