<P>
   SCOTUS-PRAYER _ The court ruled that public schools cannot let
students lead stadium crowds in prayer before high school football
games. The 6-3 decision in a Texas case said such prayers violate
the constitutionally required separation of government and
religion. The decision could carry enormous significance beyond
football games or other high school sports events. (Perkes/Trower,
Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
