John Lewis of Georgia introduce legislation putting Congress on
record as apologizing for its ``role in promoting and sustaining
slavery.'' The introduction of the legislation is timed to
commemorate the anniversary of the date (June 19, 1865) when word
reached the last slaves still in bondage that the Civil War had
ended and they were free. (Montgomery, Cox News Service). WITH
