SCI-ELEPHANTS-REPEL -- Dr. Ferrel Loki Osborn loves elephants. But
he also loves the villagers of the Zambezi River Valley in northern
Zimbabwe, whose fields of corn, cotton, and banana crops have long
tempted elephants looking for a convenient midnight snack. Isborn
has devised a multi-pronged array of repellants, some of which
rural farmers can concoct themselves, all using capsaicin, the
chemical that puts the heat in hot peppers. Elephants in Zimbabwe
climb over an electric fence to get at crops. (Courtesy of Ferrel
