<HEADLINE>
ANOTHER SUSPECT ARRESTED IN CENTRAL PARK ATTACK 
</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ The police arrested a 17-year-old from Queens on
Monday in connection with the June 11 attacks on women in Central
Park, bringing the number of men arrested to 18.
</P>
<P>
   The youth, Dellon Evans, was charged with felony sexual abuse
and riot, said Barbara Thompson, a spokeswoman for the Manhattan
district attorney's office.
</P>
<P>
   Evans, who was one of the suspects whose photographs, taken from
videos of the attack, were circulated in the media by the police,
turned himself in, said Lt. Dennis Cirillo, a police spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   Cirillo did not have details on what Evans is accused of doing
in the chaos after the National Puerto Rican Day Parade, during
which crowds of men doused women with water and sexually molested
them in the southeastern corner of the park.
</P>
<P>
   Four more women reported Monday that they had been sexually
abused, Cirillo said, making a total of 53 women who have now
reported that they were groped, stripped or otherwise abused.
Fourteen of the women were also victims of robberies or attempted
robberies, the lieutenant said.
</P>
<P>
   Counting Evans, six of the 17 men whose photographs were
released have now been arrested, Cirillo said.
</P>
<P>
   The attacks have prompted widespread criticism of the police,
who were said by victims to have stood by while the men were
marauding.
</P>
</TEXT>
